  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the ground beef and cook until browned, breaking it up into small pieces as it cooks.",
    "Add the onion, garlic, cinnamon, namul blanch seasoning, paprika, salt, and black pepper to the skillet and cook until the onion is translucent.",
    "Add the potatoes and carrots to the skillet and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Use a spatula to press down on the ingredients and create a crispy crust on the bottom of the skillet.",
    "Continue cooking the ingredients for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Transfer the skillet to the oven and bake at 400 degrees Fahrenheit for 15 minutes.",
    "Remove the skillet from the oven and garnish with fresh parsley before serving."
